  "special": {
    "title": "It's a Madhouse! A MADHOUSE!!!",
    "description": "Shots randomly sway left and right or up and down in flight. On impact, each projectile splits into two ricocheting rounds that gain speed with every bounce. It also carries a large damage boost, plus increased accuracy and magazine size."
  },
  "notes": "It performs poorly at distance but can blanket an area if you aim at the ground in the middle of a group, especially in tight arenas. The ricochets split at fixed angles, so Gaige's Close Enough tends to work poorly because the split rounds often veer past the target. Shots are absorbed by ION Loader shields, while Buzzard towers can serve as reliable banking surfaces for hitting Buzzards.",
